# Stuff Docker should never copy into the build context — keeps the
# image small and avoids stale local state poisoning the build.

# Build artefacts
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/htmlcov
**/.coverage
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/dist
**/build
**/*.egg-info

# Node stuff that creeps into the SDK skills tree during local dev
**/node_modules

# Local SQLite + uploads + per-user twin state — these belong to the
# DEPLOYED instance's /data volume, not the source tree.
**/rune_server.db
**/rune_server.db-*
**/.nexus
**/.nexus_server
**/twins
**/uploads
**/.rune_cache

# Dotnet / desktop project — the server image doesn't need any of it.
packages/desktop

# Local env files (we mount .env via docker-compose, not COPY)
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.development

# Editor / git
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
.idea
**/*.swp
**/.DS_Store

# Logs
**/*.log
**/logs
